comments.body:
Split this comment up:

```suggestion
        // Calculate all conflicting entries and enforce BIP125 rule 5.
        if (!GetEntriesForRBF(tx, m_pool, setIterConflicting, state, allConflicting)) return false;
        // Enforce BIP125 rule 2.
        if (!HasNoNewUnconfirmed(tx, m_pool, setIterConflicting, state)) return false;
```

(The comment is added in 28e7da0363 _MOVEONLY: getting mempool conflicts to policy/rbf_, which is a bit confusing since it implies that `GetEntriesForRBF()` enforces rule 2)

